data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func`, not `Expression<Func>`

Your manual expression tree won't compile anymore. The good news: you no longer need it.

```csharp
// EF Core 10 ŌĆö replaces all that Expression.Lambda/Expression.Call code
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type columns ŌĆö names are now uniquified & nested paths changed

**Same-level:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one column silently. Now EF appends a number (e.g. `Street1`). If you rely on a shared column or need stable names, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});
```

**Nested:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was column `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (full path). To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

> **Important:** If you have existing migrations, these renames will generate migration diffs. Pin column names with `HasColumnName` to avoid unwanted schema changes.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gains a `string logCommandText` parameter (contains potentially-redacted SQL for logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
